🧭 Project Overview

In this project, we use Terraform to provision an Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud) instance, which represents a virtual server in AWS. This is a foundational DevOps skill because EC2 instances are used to run applications, services, and backend systems in the cloud.

Instead of manually launching servers from the AWS Console, we define and deploy infrastructure using Infrastructure as Code (IaC).

🎯 Objective
Launch an EC2 instance using Terraform
Attach key pair for SSH access
Associate security groups for network control
Understand cloud compute provisioning
Learn how compute resources are managed as code

🧰 Technologies Used
Technology	Purpose
Terraform	Infrastructure as Code
