Implementation
Step 1: Configure AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}
Step 2: Reference Existing Key Pair (from Day 1)
resource "aws_key_pair" "devops_kp" {
  key_name   = "devops-kp"
  public_key = file("~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub")
}
Step 3: Create Security Group (from Day 2)
resource "aws_security_group" "ec2_sg" {
  name        = "ec2-security-group"
  description = "Allow SSH and HTTP traffic"

  ingress {
    description = "SSH Access"
    from_port   = 22
    to_port     = 22
    protocol    = "tcp"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }

  ingress {
    description = "HTTP Access"
    from_port   = 80
    to_port     = 80
    protocol    = "tcp"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }

  egress {
    from_port   = 0
    to_port     = 0
    protocol    = "-1"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }
}
Step 4: Launch EC2 Instance
resource "aws_instance" "web_server" {
  ami           = "ami-0c101f26f147fa7fd"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  key_name = aws_key_pair.devops_kp.key_name

  vpc_security_group_ids = [
    aws_security_group.ec2_sg.id
  ]

  tags = {
    Name = "devops-ec2"
  }
}
Explanation
ami
ami = "ami-0c101f26f147fa7fd"

Defines the operating system image used to launch the instance.

instance_type
instance_type = "t2.micro"

Specifies compute resources (CPU + memory).

key_name
key_name = aws_key_pair.devops_kp.key_name

Attaches SSH key for secure login.

vpc_security_group_ids
vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.ec2_sg.id]

Attaches firewall rules to the instance.

Step 5: Initialize Terraform
terraform init
Step 6: Validate Configuration
terraform validate
Step 7: Preview Infrastructure
terraform plan
Step 8: Deploy EC2 Instance
terraform apply

Confirm:

yes
Step 9: Verify Deployment
terraform state list

Expected output:

aws_instance.web_server
aws_key_pair.devops_kp
aws_security_group.ec2_sg
